Dr. Jill Biden spoke at the OJJDP National Conference on the topic of supporting military families and the importance of mentoring for military children. She highlighted the challenges that military children face, such as frequent moves and deployments, and shared a personal story of a teenager named Angela whose father was deployed to Afghanistan. Dr. Biden emphasized the need for teachers, counselors, and classmates to show support and understanding to military children. She also mentioned the Department of Justice's partnership with the Department of Defense to award $20 million to organizations providing mentoring services to military children. Dr. Biden concluded by urging the audience to consider how they can contribute to bringing stability, guidance, and friendship into the lives of military families.